From: Govindarajulu Varadarajan <_govind@gmx.com>
Date: Mon, 23 Jun 2014 16:07:59 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 14/56] enic: fix return value in _vnic_dev_cmd
Patch-mainline: v3.17-rc1
Git-commit: 10cc88446cec4eee8e2efab24ad387d52ef1f4fb
References: bsc#922871 fate#318754

Hardware (in readq(&devcmd->args[0])) returns positive number in case of error.
But _vnic_dev_cmd should return a negative value in case of error.

Signed-off-by: Govindarajulu Varadarajan <_govind@gmx.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: Gary Ching-Pang Lin <glin@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/cisco/enic/vnic_dev.c |    4 ++--
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/cisco/enic/vnic_dev.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/cisco/enic/vnic_dev.c
@@ -312,12 +312,12 @@ static int _vnic_dev_cmd(struct vnic_dev
 				err = (int)readq(&devcmd->args[0]);
 				if (err == ERR_EINVAL &&
 				    cmd == CMD_CAPABILITY)
-					return err;
+					return -err;
 				if (err != ERR_ECMDUNKNOWN ||
 				    cmd != CMD_CAPABILITY)
 					pr_err("Error %d devcmd %d\n",
 						err, _CMD_N(cmd));
-				return err;
+				return -err;
 			}
 
 			if (_CMD_DIR(cmd) & _CMD_DIR_READ) {
